SUMMARY:Trees and People Coalition's Canopy Awards
DESCRIPTION:Join us for Tree and People Coalitions’ Canopy Awards! \nCelebrating works of architects\, landscape designers\, developers\, urban planners\, community organizations and educators within the greater Seattle metropolitan area that:\n• Demonstrate an outstanding commitment to the preservation and planting of urban trees\n• Thoughtfully integrate buildings within their existing site context and environmental conditions\n• Develop educational programs that enrich and engage the community\, with a primary emphasis on creating healthy urban environments. \nOpen to ages 12+. Children ages 12-17 must be accompanied by a guardian. No pets. No outside food or beverages – venue refreshments only. \nRegister \nLearn more about Trees and People Coalition here.
URL:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/trees-and-people-coalitions-canopy-awards/
LOCATION:The Georgetown Stables\, 980 S Nebraska Street\, Seattle\, WA\, 98108\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/banner_draft_2.png
END:VEVENT
